{{Orphan|date=November 2016}}

[[File:Fulani herd in the dust.jpg|thumb|225x225px|The Fulani are [[pastoralism|pastoral]] cattle herders and so one of their traditional proverbs is "If the cattle die, the ''[[Fulbe]]'' will die".{{sfn|Patterson|1959|p=186}}]]
'''Fulani  proverbs''' are the folk wisdom of the [[Fulani people]], expressed in their traditional sayings such as "''munyal deefan hayre''" (patience can cook a stone).

