'''Meade Layne''' (September 8, 1882{{spaced ndash}}May 12, 1961)<ref name="bsrf-1">{{cite web |url= http://research.borderlands.com/wiki/Meade_Layne |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120101011542/http://research.borderlands.com/wiki/Meade_Layne |archivedate= January 1, 2012 |title= Borderland Sciences Research Associates |work= borderlands.com |publisher= Borderland Sciences Research Foundation |date= |accessdate= }}</ref> was an early researcher of [[ufology]] and [[parapsychology]], best known for proposing an early version of the [[interdimensional hypothesis]] to explain [[flying saucer]] sightings.{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=16}} Layne was the founder and first director of Borderland Sciences Research Associates.<ref>{{cite book |chapter= The Case for the 'Critters' |last= Constable |first= Trevor James |title= Other Worlds, Other Universes |editor1-last= Steiger |editor1-first= Brad |editor2-last= White |editor2-first= John |publisher= Health Research Books |isbn= 9780787312916 |pages= [https://books.google.com/books?id=vgQj5D524PYC&pg=PA71&lpg=PA70 70–2]}}</ref> Prior to his public work studying ufos, Layne was professor at the [[University of Southern California]], and English department head at [[Illinois Wesleyan University]] and [[Florida Southern College]].<ref name="bsrf-1"/>

=="Etheria"==
Layne speculated that, rather than representing advanced [[military]] or [[Extraterrestrial life|extraterrestrial]] technology, flying saucers were piloted by beings from a [[Multiverse|parallel dimension]], which he called Etheria, and their "ether ships" were usually [[invisibility|invisible]] but could be seen when their [[atom]]ic motion became slow enough.{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=16}}<ref name="Davis2006">{{cite book |last= Davis |first= Erik |title= The Visionary State: A Journey Through California's Spiritual Landscape |chapter= Space Brothers |year= 2006 |publisher= [[Chronicle Books]] |isbn= 9780811848350 |page= [https://books.google.com/books?id=EQzj3rAWWtEC&pg=PA192 192]}}</ref> He further claimed that Etherians could become stranded on the [[Earth|terrestrial plane]] when their ether ships malfunctioned,{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=17}} and that various governments were aware of these incidents and had investigated them.{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=17}}

Furthermore, Layne argued that [[Etherians]] and their ether ships inspired much of earth's [[mythology]] and [[religion]],{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=16}} but that they were truly mortal beings despite having a high level of technological and spiritual advancement.{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=16}} He claimed that their motive in coming to the terrestrial plane of existence was to [[UFO religion|reveal]] their accumulated wisdom to humanity.{{sfn|Reece|2007|pp=16-7}} These revelations would be relayed through individuals with sufficiently developed [[psychic]] abilities, allowing them to contact the Etherians and communicate with them directly;{{sfn|Reece|2007|p=17}}<ref name="Greenfield2006">{{cite book |last= Greenfield |first= Allen |title =Secret Cipher of the UFOnauts |year= 2006 |publisher= [[Lulu.com]] |isbn= 9781411667594 |page= [https://books.google.com/books?id=Ws2Oemi1gKIC&pg=PA13 13] |ref= {{SfnRef|Greenfield|2006}}}}</ref> in particular, he relied extensively on the mediumship of [[Mark Probert]] as confirmation of his theories.<ref name="Probert1975">{{cite book |last= Probert |first= Mark |url={{Google books|9urAoGP4X10C|page= xv |plainurl=yes}} |title=The Magic Bag |year= 1963 |publisher= Kethra E'Da Foundation|location=San Diego|isbn= 9781585092581|at= Foreword pp. xv-xviii |contribution= Note Concerning the Mark Probert Mediumship |contributor-last= Layne|contributor-first= Meade}}</ref>

