{{citations|date=November 2013}}{{otherpeople}}
'''William Griggs''' was a [[physician|doctor]] in the village of [[Salem, Massachusetts]]. He is best known as the doctor who diagnosed the villagers of Salem as "possessed", during the time of the [[Salem witch trials]].<ref name=UVA>{{cite web|title=Important Persons in the Salem Court Records|url=http://salem.lib.virginia.edu/people?group.num=all&mbio.num=mb47|website=Salem Witch Trials Documentary Archive|publisher=Benjamin Ray and The University of Virginia|accessdate=27 November 2014|ref=UVA}}</ref> Griggs was in charge of diagnosing and determining how "much" of a witch they were. He would then send them to be tried, often found guilty, and executed. Griggs claimed that the "afflicted" girls were "under an Evil hand" (most likely referring to the [[Devil]]).

